history.text: Hi there!
Hello!
How are you today?
Good, how are you?
Do you have any plans for the day?
I'm great! I'm babysitting today so just playing with the kiddos. What about you?
I am getting ready to go to bed, I work the night shift.
Do you like animated movies?
Yes I do!
Have you ever seen Toy Story?
No I haven't. What is it about?
It's about toys that come to life, it stars a pull string cowboy named Woody who is kind of the favorite toy of the main character named Andy.
Oh that sounds interesting! I always wondered as a kid what it would be like to have your toys come to life lol
But Woody's life gets interrupted when Andy gets a new toy at his birthday, named Buzz Lightyear. Buzz thinks hes an actual space ranger and not a toy!
Oh goodness!
Tim Allen plays Buzz Lightyear and Tom Hanks is Woody.
Those are great choices for voices!
There is also a character named Mr Potato Head, a slinky dog, and a nervous green Tyrannasaurus rex.
How cool that they added Mr Potato Head lol
Buzz becomes one of Andy's favorite toys and Woody begins to feel left out, so Woody decides to trap him, that doesn't work and they both end up at a pizza place for a family outing.
This sounds like an interesting adventure! I need to see this movie!

At the pizza place Buzz still thinks that he is a space ranger, despite woody trying to convince him otherwise, and they end up stuck inside a crane game, where Andy's toy-killing neighbor Sid ends up winning them in the crane game.
A toy-killing neighbor? That sounds scary for the toys!
Sid takes the two toys home and they end up meeting a bunch of other toys that sid had torn apart, and they become really scared, but they end up escaping.
I'm glad they escaped! Sounds like they could have ended up in a bad situation if they hadn't!
After they escape, Andy's family ends up moving and the two toys almost miss the moving truck to get out, but they hope on a toy car to catch the truck.
I bet Andy would have been heartbroken to have left them behind!
I bet he would've. It then shows that they are at Christmas day, and they are all freaking out because they think that Andy might get a new toy to replace them. But Andy doesn't... he gets.. A PUPPY
Aww that's awesome!

uid2response.feedback: The other user explained the movie very well to me. They used words and explanations that would be easy for people of all ages to understand easily.
